### Description

I have a person object with an optional Address that somehow looks like this:

export class Person {
  id: number = 0;
  age: number = 0;
  name: string = '';  
  address?: Address = { street: '', city: '', postalCode: '' };
}

My approach would be to type the form somehow like this:

export interface PersonFormType {
  id: FormControl<number | null>;
  name: FormControl<string | null>;
  age: FormControl<number | null>;
  address?: FormGroup<{
    street: FormControl<string | null>;
    city: FormControl<string | null>;
    postalCode: FormControl<string | null>;
  }>;

and assign the value like this:

    this.personForm = this.fb.group({
      id: [this.person.id],
      name: [this.person.name, Validators.required],
      age: [this.person.age],     
      address: this.fb.group({
        street: [this.person.address?.street],
        city: [this.person.address?.city],
        postalCode: [this.person.address?.postalCode],
      }),
    });

which gives an err that can not be read properly because it is shortend:

Type 'FormGroup<{ id: FormControl<number | null>; name: FormControl<string | null>; age: FormControl<number | null>; address: FormGroup<{ street: FormControl<string | null | undefined>; city: FormControl<...>; postalCode: FormControl<...>; }>; }>' is not assignable to type 'FormGroup<PersonFormType>'.
  Types of property 'controls' are incompatible.
    Type '{ id: FormControl<number | null>; name: FormControl<string | null>; age: FormControl<number | null>; address: FormGroup<{ street: FormControl<string | null | undefined>; city: FormControl<...>; postalCode: FormControl<...>; }>; }' is not assignable to type 


Please provide an advanced sample in the docs on how to type forms with nested optional objects and maybe make error messages fully expandable (in VS Code)

